Pre-Game Insights: The Phillies would like to have home-field advantage through the NLCS and World Series.
If the Phillies advance to the World Series, they currently would have home-field advantage over every AL team.
Ranger Suárez allowed six runs on seven hits and two walks in two innings in Friday night’s loss to the Nats.
Zack Wheeler can make voters think harder about his candidacy with a strong performance on Saturday evening against the Nationals.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Phillies clinched the NL East on Monday.
They clinched a first-round bye in the postseason on Wednesday.
Others: Suárez is just 2-3 with a 5.74 ERA (20 earned runs in 31 1/3 innings) in seven starts since he rejoined the rotation on Aug. 24 following a month-long stint on the injured list because of a bad back.
Aaron Nola pitches Sunday. He needs only 5 2/3 innings to reach 200 innings.
Trea Turner needs one stolen base for 20, which would give him the fourth 20-20 season of his career.
Alec Bohm needs five RBIs for 100.
Brandon Marsh needs two stolen bases for 20.
Kyle Schwarber enters Saturday batting.249. Nick Castellanos is batting.254. Finishing.250 or better would carry significance to either player.
